ard to Thelma and Louise—Felski brings the language of attachment into the academy. Hooked returns us to the fundamentals of aesthetic experience, showing that the social meanings of artworks are generated not just by critics, but also by the responses of captivated audiences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAesthetics. 0aExperience. 0aHermeneutics. 0aInterest (Psychology) 0aInterest (Psychology). 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226729770423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226729770.jpg  a978-3-11-069309-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles